cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on security vulnerabilities in smart contracts on Ethereum and proposes security analysis methods to detect these vulnerabilities. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses software flaws in designing and implementing smart contracts. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper mentions the Solidity language used for programming smart contracts on Ethereum. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the distributed data storage aspect of smart contracts on blockchains. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of software tools for detecting vulnerabilities in smart contracts.
